<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 15984.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">O’Brien</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-09"><hi rend="italic">October 9,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root instructs Mr. O’Brien to request the provisional arrest and
                            detention of Yoshitaro Abe, who is charged with forgery in Hawaii, where
                            warrant has been issued, and who is understood to be under arrest at
                            Yokohama.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>